## TypeScript Standards

### Props Definition
Always use TypeScript generics for props definition:
```typescript
const props = defineProps<{
  id: string;
  data: NodeData;
  isEditing?: boolean;
}>();
```

**Never use:**
```typescript
// ‚ùå Avoid object-style props definition
const props = defineProps({
  id: {
    type: String,
    required: true
  }
});
```

### Type Imports
Use `import type` for type-only imports:
```typescript
import type { Story, Scene, SceneTransition } from '~/server/utils/db';
```

### Ref Typing
Properly type refs and reactive data:
```typescript
const items = ref<Item[]>([]);
const loading = ref<boolean>(false);
const selectedId = ref<string | null>(null);
```

### Database Types
Always use types from `~/server/utils/db` for consistency:
```typescript
import type { Story, Scene, SceneTransition } from '~/server/utils/db';
```

